<br>
Lol been camping the pained soul.. gives one a lot of time.<br>
<br>
Greedy me camping something green to me:P<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If you don't see this you play the game for a different reason than I<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I play the game to have fun and to help my comrades. Why do you play?<br>
<br>
I suppose you would refuse to help a comrade or guildmate who needed something that it would be much easier for you to get for them than it would be for them. That's not the kind of person I am tho.<br>
<br>
The fact is everyone needs help, a LOT of help to get their epic drops. How much does a Druid contribute to killing Jade reavers? How much does a Wiz contribute to killing the EG? They go on a raid and win a roll or someone else wins a roll when they aren't there and they get it MQ'd if the piece is not droppable. Pally's have gone on burn raids to loot a book, they can even help by holding aggro, lowering the risk of wiping.<br>
<br>
They may have been one of 30 or one of 6 or even not there.. what is particularly significant about this?<br>
<br>
The shocker is that some high AA characters are more help in some situations than mid fifties characters.<br>
<br>
Who does this really hurt? Individuals are getting the drops they need that much faster. Mid level guilds can more easily mobilize because for every burner they have that they can get there thats about 5 less 55's they need. People in uber guilds who mostly cannot be bothered to kill these mobs now have a viable option to complete their epics.<br>
<br>
Who is suffering? Really?<br>
<br>
The guildleaders of melee centric mid level guilds that mistreated their casters and are now finding they have a lot less power to decide who gets what epic drops.<br>
<br>
I don't see anyone else suffering, on Quelious anyway.<br>
<br>
To those guildleaders I will just say: things change. Send a tell to your wizzies sometimes and say hi when you don't need a port. Ask how they are doing. Invite them on a fear raid, and not always hate raids. For that matter be nice to your mages and necros. Just be nice to people, period, and your guild won't get lopsided.<br>
<br>
FK <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/udjjinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>djjinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(6/27/02 1:23:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=323.topic&index=263>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This may touch some nerves, but WTF lets see what happen</span><hr size=1> ok, I think people need to look at the big picture, at least IMHO.<br>
<br>
This seems to be about classes that get one big ability that tends to dominate in raids.<br>
<br>
First Warriors got defensive, which allows them to take a lot more damage and still keep aggro.  Lots of people thought this was overpowered.  With this ability and CH, a mob can be kept on a single target and under control, allowing huge mobs to be dealt with in realitively smaller groups than before.<br>
<br>
VI had two choices, they could nerf defensive, or adjust mobs around it and increase the power of other toons so they catch up with the warrior.  VI had a long history of nerfs and taking flack from those nerfs.  VI decided not to nerf defensive.  Therefore other toons need to be upped in power.<br>
<br>
With AA, warriors didn't get much in class abilities, nothing really overpowering.  Seems like AoE taunt is the nicest, but really just a convenient ability, nothing overpowering.  Some toons though were targeted for upgrade it seems.<br>
<br>
Wizzards got MB, and like wizzards, nothing subtle.  Because of this, it is going to be one of the first &quot;class defining&quot; abilities to be noticed.  One note here, MB takes alot of post 60 work to get to, unlike defensive which comes along to every warrior at level 55.<br>
<br>
Chanters, necros and druids got dire charm.  A bit more subtle, and with limitations, but potentially as deadly if not more deadly than MB.  Mobs are alot more powerful than toons, and properly controled and buffed, can do alot more for alot longer than a wizzard manaburn.  Of course this is only starting to be of concern, again because it takes a while to get the AA for it, and longer to really know how to use it.<br>
<br>
Rangers got increased arrow damage and endless quiver.  I'm speculating here, but it seems like a group of rangers on the fastest horses and best arrows can kite about anything if they have the room for it and it doesn't summon.<br>
<br>
What does all this mean?  Well VI can either nerf, or try to pull all the other classes up to the highest power classes.  Given VI's recent trends, I would say they won't nerf.  This means that people start complaining about the how unfair the other classes abilities are, and with the next expansion, other classes get &quot;class defining abilites&quot;.  Also mobs will be tuned to provide more of a challenge to these abilities.  Look to see even more mobs summon and hp to go up even more.  Maybe even special abilites or resistances to compensate.  Then those abilities become manditory to take down the uber mobs.<br>
<br>
The moral of this is that one class seeming to overpower other classes is just part of the cycle of evolving and not nerfing.  The first toons to get the treatment will be left behind as new toons get the treatment, kinda like computer upgrades, those that got the latest will be the best.  The first ones to get it won't get upgraded until everyone else gets the treatment.<br>
<br>
When PoP comes out, I predict mages will dominate the game (but maybe I'm wrong <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
Is manaburn too powerful?  I guess it just seems that way to alot of people at the moment.  It won't stay dominant. People will discover other dominant abilities, and with upgrades class x will dominate with special ability y.  Just the way the cycle goes.<br>
<br>
