 <p><center><img src="http://www.lotuscult.com/~masadala/palasig.jpg" </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uwadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wadin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(6/28/02 4:22:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=323.topic&index=278>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This may touch some nerves, but WTF lets see what happen</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> i]Palazious said[/i]<br>
PS. Garaddor and Sephrok are just examples for Montty's learning curve. As far as I know, they are respectable people and this isnt to paint them as 'farmers' by Montty's definition, As we all know that most guilds/people use this same method for selling excess item. I apologize in advance for using you as examples and it will not happen again.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I believe that both Garaddor and Sephrok are guild leaders for their respected guilds. As such, they would have the authority and possible need to sell excessive guild items that the whole guild may have received over time in its actions. What they are selling by far does not indicated any farming what so ever, IMO. It indicates an active raiding guild with excessive amount of items. The majority of the guilds on our servers do this as a given.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Palazious said</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
2 ) Spells... The allusive Sunstrike which I've been trying for 5 months to get comes off of them.. as well as other 60 spells I'm still lacking.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Just to let you know, Palazious. Sunstrike does drop from the Guardian Wurms in Skyfire. We got Ylferdin his copy last week while camping Ragefire for Mysses. We actually had a very good set of spells received while camping Ragefire from these Guardian Wurms. We received Tears of Prexus and Sunstrike for Ylferdin, Torpor and Malo for Tapes as well as several other high level shaman, druid, cleric and enchanter spells.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Montague said</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Just because manaburn isn't being abused (yet) on our server doesn't mean that it isn't being abused  elsewhere. I now change my stance on the issue and think that there should be a nerf on manaburn. I think they should make it NOT work on mobs that are flagged as *dragon* and have less than 32001hp.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
While this is very possible as to a way they could reduce the effectiveness of manaburn, I personally think this would be the worse way. As I stated before, the best trait of manaburn is that it is available to small guilds to use in what to them would be major raid events. As Gurunt is stating, these dragons ARE major events to some small guilds. Manaburn allows them to possibly defeat these events easier. Restricting it to not work on mobs that are flagged as a dragon would be restricting it from working on the mobs that you would only use it on. Lets face it, no manaburning wizard would use their ability on a spider in Velks. No, they will save it for the major (to them) event that they could possibly participate in within the next hour.<br>
<br>
I think the major thing that most people have with manaburn is not necessarily that is does major damage. Wizards are supposed to do major damage. It is that this major damage is stackable with other wizards and is cummalative with them. That makes it possible for a group of wizards to do something that no other single group can do. Kill a Kunark (or Velious) dragon without the possibility of that dragon getting a counter-attack. If there was a way to make it so that these mobs could get a counter-attack against a group of wizards using manaburn, I believe the reasonable people who dislike the current state of manaburn will have no problem with it. The only way I see for this to be possible is if they placed a 1 tick buff on the mob it was casted against. This removes that insta-kill technique that is currently occurring with 6 (or 12) wizards that seems to upset so many people. It removes the stack-ability of manaburn.<br>
<br>
-Wadin Pureheart of Quellious<br>
Warder<br>
<br>
PS&gt; Rather if manaburn should be nerfed or not and rather if our own wizard in the Quellious community are abusing the ability, I personally believe that manaburn WILL be nerfed. Why? Because it IS being abused on other servers, and Verant generally does not make a change to a class ability that affects only a couple servers. It is sad, but it is true. And I do not think Graffe website is helping much with changing this state. From what I seen, it has been more of a challenged to see which server can do much bigger and more showy things with the ability over on that site.<br>
<br>
