<br>
There was an incident of a burn team on some server that steamrolled a raid on VS. (I forget the server but it's all there in gory detail on Graffes)<br>
<br>
The fact that guilds steamroll other guilds everyday will be overlooked, and instead it will be all burners are bad.<br>
<br>
I may be a polyanna but look at what is happenning with Ragefire.. I think this server is at least slightly better than average and I really cannot envision a burn team steamrolling a raid. Burners back down a lot and never even say anything.<br>
<br>
But the fact of the matter is when one guild steamrolls or merely honestly beats another to the punch it is because they have more powerful toons so the need to organize fewer people and are thus quicker, or else extremely good mobilization. Burn teams are just a continuation of this trend.<br>
<br>
Burn teams are easier to mobilize, on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> paper</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> but the fact is that a lot of the time these poeple are doing stuff with their own guild and are not free to flit off.<br>
<br>
A guildleader can call a drop everything, but burners have no way to push other burners.<br>
<br>
(When a lot of guilds can field burn teams in house this question will pretty much go away anyway, it will become normal to send a burn team to hit a dragon, and it will again be the same people contending as before, but that's another issue)<br>
<br>
Anyway Wadin you have some good points but you have made one incorrect assumption that seems to be rampant:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ..Kill a Kunark (or Velious) dragon without the possibility of that dragon getting a counter-attack..- Wadin<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This is unbased. Dragon fear is longer range than Manaburn and if one burner gets feared, it's a good likelihood of a wipe. If two do it's almost a certainty. It's not at all a sure thing, and if it wipes, its over. There is no do-over. In a regular raid you rez and go again. On a burn raid you pack it up.<br>
<br>
Now back to our regularly scheduled inanity rebuttal.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ..yet the majority of you still see this as some sort of pissing contest, or my penis is bigger than yer penis dispute between wizards and warriors - Montyy<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Montyy <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> you</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are the one that brought up Warriors vs Wizards.. we didn't. In fact we have been tryin to ignore this as the irrelevancy it is.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  If you really give away everything you've gotten so far from burn raids.. - Montyy<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
