<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> (sorry i find that highly dubious  ), - Montyy<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And I am not at all suprised you do. The interesting thing about people is they assume everyone else suffers from the same character deficits they have. Thus a thief is always concerned that other people are trying to steal from him and an honest person rarely is concerned until they are forced to deal with it.<br>
<br>
A greedy person cannot envision that someone else may not be greedy, and moreover it makes them uncomfortable to consider that another person might not be greedy since this spotlights their own avaricious nature. Not pleasant.<br>
<br>
Yet nevertheless not everyone is greedy.<br>
<br>
I will admit a bias to believe other people are also not greedy and perhaps thus have an overly optimistic view of my fellow burners (but i know for a fact many occasions where drops were <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> given</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to guild mates and not just by me) but I also recognize you will have a very difficult time comprehending that not everyone is as greedy as you.<br>
<br>
Which makes your whole argument very understandable, though certainly not logical.<br>
<br>
But again for the record I will categorically state I have not sold one SINGLE piece of dragon loot. Not even a spell. Nothing.<br>
<br>
I have been asked to sell. I have not sold. What little I have gotten goes to my guild. Period.<br>
<br>
This is probably unimaginable to you, but nevertheless it is a fact.<br>
<br>
Do I expect all other burners not to sell a piece from time to time? No. May I someday sell a piece that no one in my guild can use? Possibly. But it has not happenned.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> So are you saying that if I were lvl 55 and wanted a CoF or a RBB, Id have to suck up to a MB wizard to get it? - Montyy<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
